{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The serine incorporator/TMS membrane protein (TDE1/TMS) family include SERINC1-5 from mammals and its homologues membrane protein Tms1 from yeasts. Members in this family contain eleven transmembrane helices.</p>\n\n<p>SERINC1-5 function in incorporating serine into membranes and facilitating the synthesis of two serine-derived lipids, phosphatidylserine and sphingolipids [[cite:PUB00033686]]. SERINC3 (also known as TDE1) and SERINC5 are restriction factors required to restrict infectivity of lentiviruses, such as HIV-1; they act by inhibiting an early step of viral infection and they impair the penetration of the viral particle into the cytoplasm [[cite:PUB00156058], [cite:PUB00156059]]. SERINC3/5 are non-ATP-dependent, non-specific lipid transporters for phosphatidylserine, phosphatidylcholine, and phosphatidylethanolamine that functions as a scramblase that flips lipids in both directions across the membrane. Phospholipid scrambling results in HIV-1 surface exposure of phosphatidylserine and loss of membrane asymmetry, which leads to changes in HIV-1 Env conformation and loss of infectivity [[cite:PUB00156060], [cite:PUB00156061]]. SERINC3 is overexpressed in tumours [[cite:PUB00070879]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF03348" "Serine incorporator (Serinc)"}, "panther" {"PTHR10383" "SERINE INCORPORATOR"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Serine incorporator/TMS membrane protein", "short" "TDE1/TMS"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 3, "domain_architectures" 139, "proteomes" 2613, "taxa" 8947, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 12842, "sets" 0, "proteins" 12144, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 7775}, "pathways" 8}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR005016", :literature {"PUB00070879" {"URL" nil, "i